short_description: Explores the life and legacy of Mariska Hargitay's mother, Hollywood icon Jayne Mansfield, who died tragically in a car accident at age 34 when Mariska was only three years old.

facts_and_links: {'Trivia': ['The documentary delves into the tragic demise of Jayne Mansfield in a car accident in 1967, which catalyzed significant alterations to road safety regulations. The National Highway Traffic Safety Administration proposed novel standards mandating the installation of underride prevention guards on substantial large trucks, The implementation of these regulations was not finalized until 31 years later, in 1998.', 'https://www.imdb.com/title/tt36464353/trivia/?ref_=tt_dyk_trv'], 'Quotes': ["My Father: I would love to have had one more conversation with your father before he passed away, because I also would like to apologize to him because I'm sure I was also part of his suffering.Mariska Hargitay: Thank you for saying that.My Father: I'm so happy that I have been given the chance to say these things.Self - My Sister: Well, you're 89, so you'll get to tell him soon.", 'https://www.imdb.com/title/tt36464353/quotes/?ref_=tt_dyk_qu'], 'Connections': ['Features Female Jungle (1955)', 'https://www.imdb.com/title/tt36464353/movieconnections/?ref_=tt_dyk_cnn']}
